The paper deals with probabilistic transition systems and their equivalence, which are topics related to logic and automata theory. Therefore, cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the correlation between behavioural metrics and quantitative probabilistic logics, which suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper involves the study of formula evaluation and approximation, which are topics related to programming languages (cs.PL) and data structures (cs.DS).
